<h3>Story of CoursesHub</h3>
<span class="text-muted">The short version :-P</span>
<hr/>
<div class="well" style="width:800px;margin:auto;">
	<strong>Hi everyone</strong>,
	<p>I'm Vignesh (Final year ECE), one of the contributors of 'courseshub'. This is the story of the app, it all began during the NASA 2013 hackathon. During our journey to Bangalore, Shiva Nandan (aka seek), my Delta senior discussed with me about an app that will bridge the gap between faculties and students. He had already developed a prototype with very basic feature, the app with its partially finished features was already impressive. He wanted someone to work on the rest of the app and complete it. Unlike other Delta projects no one volunteered for this one. The problem was that he built the prototype with the then new technologies which no one in the club has worked on, so we were reluctant to take up the task. Shortly after Pragyan I was jobless so I volunteered and promised to complete it during summer vacations but ended up doing nothing. </p>
	<p>Due to the tough competition that I faced while getting a summer intern and the fact that I come from a non compsci branch made me fear that spending time on the app would affect my placements. Sadly I dropped out of the app and did my intern and the development process remained idle for about 6 months. </p>
	<p>I resumed my work in late October,2013. I was re-factoring code and redesigned the database schema and was passively contributing, but I was keen on persuading some of my batch mates and juniors to work on the app. The development work gained friction just before my semester exam. After spending my entire winter holidays on the app, here it is.</p>
