	<strong>To Students:</strong>
	<p>The app was completed hastily and I had no time to test it across various screen sizes and browsers. Please let me know if you feel that something is not working properly or if there is some design issue. The app is supposed to work with out any page reloads except for static pages and login page. If you find anything wrong please let me know, don't hesitate to contact me, it can even be very simple like a box not having a rounded corner. </p>

	<strong>To Faculties:</strong>
	<p>I know that it is a burden on you and you definetly have to put in extra effort to record all the class activities but on the brighter side you have to do it only once and the records will be maintained for years. Even after 10 years you will be able see what you have taught and what the questions were like. This would be helpful during accrediation process.</p>

	<strong>To Critics:</strong>
	<p>Some people say that you guys are good for nothing and you can only talk and never do something abt it,  but I'm a little open minded. I think you guys play an important role in the evolution of the app and help us maintain high standards. I'm open to critism, please mail me if you have anything or if you choose to be anonymous put it up on NITT Confessions.</p>

	<strong>To Developers:</strong>
	<p>The app is still short on man power. Any opensource contribution is deeply appriciated. Source code is available on github, if you are interested in learning about the app or contributing to it, please contact me. </p>

	<strong>To Hackers/Crackers:</strong>
	<p>I think the app has all precautionary measure to shield it from any kind of attack. As far as I know the app has protection against CSRF, XSS, SQL Injection, etc. You mighthave guessed from the source but still, backbone and bootstrap on the front end, rails 4 on the back end deployed using unicorn server with 2 simultaneos process workers, usual rails app memory footprint, MySQL database and paperclip gem for image processing . All the best!</p>
